I used to be like this, but I have recently warmed to this idea.  foo.bar( baz ) is a little "verbose looking", but when you generalize to arbitrary expressions:<p><pre><code>   foo.bar( baz => quux, gorch => 42 );
</code></pre>
it starts looking a lot nicer.  The foo.bar(baz) is really the outlier, and for the sake of consistency, you might as well add a space.<p>(That said, sometimes I don't, and I would never "care" one way or the other.  If you are writing good code, where the spaces are is of little importance.)
